The Nigeria Police Force (NPF), Kogi State  Command  has confirmed arrest of  six suspects in connection with the killing of one Mrs Salome Abu, at Ochadamu, Ofu Local Government Area (LGA) of the state, on Nov. 18. The spokesman for the command, DSP William Aya disclosed this while speaking in Lokoja on Monday. Aya said that the suspects were brought in on Friday. Abu, a former councillor and Women Leader of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) was set ablaze on Nov. 18 in her husbandâ€™s house at Ochadamu, by hoodlums. Aya said the police had started interogating the suspects to ascertain their level of culpability in the death of the woman. He said that the outcome of the investigation wound be made public as soon as it was completed.